               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>The Harry K. Eustace Papers consist of a journal illustrated with pen-and-ink drawings which depict Eustace's hunting and survival skills. Photographs of Eustace and jungle animals are also included in the collection, as well as a flyer advertising his lecture/film, "My African Hunt in War Time." The papers were purchased in 1991.</p>
